Mouthparts. Buccal cone short. Labrum non-ogival. Labium with 11 chaetae: a1, a2, p2, E, F, G, b, c, d, e and f. Labial papillae x not detected (
Fig. 30
). Maxilla styliform (
Fig. 35
), mandible with five teeth, being two basal stronger, unequal teeth and three unequal apical teeth (
Fig. 36
).

Ventral chaetotaxy. On head, groups Vea, Vem and Vep with 3, 3, 1 chaetae respectively; group Vi with 5 chaetae (
Fig 30
). On Abd IV, furcal vestige with 4 chaetae, devoid of mi but with a small posterior area of primary granulation. Ventral chaeta L' on Abd V absent (
Figs. 26–27
). Male with thick and forked chaetae (male ventral organ) on Abd IV: 2Vei and 2Vec (
Fig. 34
).
